.TH SMARTRPMSORT 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-utils" "SmartMet Build Tools"
.SH NAME
smartrpmsort \- keep only the newest RPM of each package, archive the rest
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smartrpmsort
.I directory
.RI [ subdirectory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smartrpmsort
scans
.I directory
for files matching
.BI * - version - release . arch .rpm
.RB ( x86_64 " or " noarch ),
groups them by package name, picks the highest version\(hyrelease pair
in each group as the keeper, and moves all older copies into a
subdirectory of
.IR directory .
.PP
The default subdirectory name is
.BR archive ;
a different name may be supplied as the second argument. The
subdirectory is created on demand and is left empty if no archiving
is necessary.
.PP
Sorting is numeric and dotted: the version field is split on
.RB \(lq . \(rq,
each component is zero\(hypadded to five digits, and up to five
components are concatenated to form the sort key.
Filenames that do not parse against the expected RPM naming pattern
are reported and skipped.
.PP
Exit status is
.B 0
on success and
.B 1
if any
.BR rename (2)
operation failed.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I directory
Directory containing the RPM files to sort.
.TP
.I subdirectory
Name of the archive subdirectory. Defaults to
.BR archive .
.SH EXAMPLES
Keep only the newest of each
.B smartmet-*
RPM in a download directory, moving older ones into
.BR archive/ :
.PP
.RS 4
smartrpmsort ~/Downloads/smartmet
.RE
.PP
Use a custom archive name:
.PP
.RS 4
smartrpmsort /var/cache/smartmet old
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smartbuild (1),
.BR rpm (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-utils/issues>.
